# .dockerignore
#
# Keeps unnecessary or sensitive files out of the Docker build context,
# so they can never end up copied into the image.

# Installed dependencies are always built fresh INSIDE the container
# (for the container's OS/architecture) — a local copy would be wrong.
node_modules

# The real secrets file. Must never enter the image. Configuration is
# injected at `docker run` time instead (see Dockerfile comments).
.env

# Version control history has no purpose inside a running container and
# would needlessly bloat the build context.
.git
.gitignore

# npm debug output, irrelevant to the built image.
npm-debug.log*

# The Docker build instructions themselves don't need to exist inside
# the image they produce.
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
